{{see|UT}}
==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''ut'', from the first word of ''Ut queant laxis'', a medieval hymn, where the first word in each line was taken to use for the names of the syllables of [[sol-fa]]

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌt|-ʌt]]

===Noun===
'''ut'''

# syllable formerly used in [[sol-fa]] to represent the first note of a [[major scale]].  '''Ut''' has been replaced by ''[[do]]''.

